Vakhidov, Jakhongir (2527) - Shogdzhiev, Roman (2042)
FIDE World Rapid Championship (chess24.com) [1] 2023.12.26
D10 Queen's Gambit Declined Slav defence, exchange variation

1.c4 c6 2.d4 d5 3.cxd5 cxd5 4.Bf4 Nf6 5.e3 Nc6 6.Bd3 Bg4 7.f3 Bd7 8.Nc3 e6 9.g4 Be7 10.Nge2 O-O 11.Kf2 Ne8 12.h4 Nd6 13.a3 f5 14.g5 Rc8 15.Qc2 Na5 16.b3 Be8 17.Qb2 b5 18.Rac1 a6 19.Bg3 Ne4+ 20.Bxe4 fxe4 21.Nf4 Bd7 22.fxe4 dxe4 23.Kg2 e5 24.dxe5 Bg4 25.Ncd5 Qd7 26.Kh2 Bf3 27.e6 Qb7 28.Rxc8 Rxc8 29.Rc1 Rxc1 30.Qxc1 Bd6 31.Qd2 Nc6 32.Nf6+ gxf6 33.Qxd6 fxg5 34.Nd5 Qg7 35.Bf2 gxh4 36.Nf4 Qb2 37.Nh3 Qg7 38.Nf4 Qb2 39.Nh3 Qg7 40.Nf4 Qa1 41.Ng2 Qf1 42.Nxh4 Qxf2+ 43.Kh3 Qf1+ 44.Kh2 Qh1+ 45.Kg3 Qg1+ 46.Kh3 Bg4

Timestamps:
00:00 Hello Everyone!

The FIDE World Rapid Championship is a 13-round Swiss tournament taking place from 26–28 December 2022 in Almaty, Kazakhstan. The prize fund is $350,000, with a $60,000 top prize.

Players receive 15 minutes for the entire game, plus a 10-second increment starting from move one. A tie for 1st is decided by two 3+2 blitz games. If still tied, more 3+2 games are played until a player wins. Official website: worldrapidandblitz2022.fide.com
